“I’m gonna get this helmet off now, okay?” Silva took the girl's opposite shoulder, she
could feel the girl breathing slowly. She must’ve passed out, Dirk was a psychic as well, so it
must have been a battle. Silva grabbed the front of the helmet, it seemed to be metal, and was
shaped like one of those old motorcycle helmets, with blank steel as goggles. She pulled the
helmet off, careful to not twist her neck.
Long black hair fell out, Silva expected the girl to wake from the movement, but it
seemed she was slowly rousing to consciousness. Silva studied her face, this didn’t make any
sense, this was her sister. Silva had never had a sister, but looking at this girl, she knew it was
her. The girl's eyes opened, revealing a bright violet color that matched Silva’s.
“Silva?” Her voice was blurry, who’s voice? Is this person my sister? I never had one
though, but this girl is my sis… Silva was caught in a loop. She felt herself actually sway back
and forth, her sister now trying to hold her up, as she fell deep into a coma of confusion.
